  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You become imbued with the blessings of the Summer Court. You are a font of energy that offers respite from injuries. You have a pool of fey energy represented by a number of d6s equal to your Druid level.</p><p>As a Bonus Action, you can choose one creature you can see within 120 feet of you and spend a number of those dice equal to half your Druid level or less. Roll the spent dice and add them together. The target regains a number of Hit Points equal to the total. The target also gains 1 Temporary Hit Point per die spent.</p><p>You regain all expended dice when you finish a Long Rest. Alternatively at 9th level, when you roll Initiative, you can choose to regain a number of expended d6s equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1) instead of an expended <em>Wild Shape</em> with your <em>Always Wild</em>.</p><section id=\"secret-g0r9We08FPldPOb3\" class=\"secret\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>The <strong>Heal</strong> activity will provide a heal for the appropriate number of d6 Hit Points, but it will not add the Temporary Hit Points, those need to be added manually.</p><p>The <strong>Regain Dice with Always Wild</strong> activity can be used to recharge your d6 pool and consume your use of Always Wild.</p></section>",
      "chat": ""
    },
